  "text": "The findings that CD157 i) is constitutively expressed by neutrophils, monocytes (5) and vascular endothelial cells [CITATION_1] , ii) is up-regulated by soluble mediators of inflammation [CITATION_2] , and iii) undergoes redistribution and membrane compartmentalization in the presence of proinflammatory cytokines [CITATION_3] , fostered the hypothesis that it could be a crucial player in the control of leukocyte migration and transmigration during the inflammatory response.",
